			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok here's an idea, now I THINK this was suggested here in this forum some time back, anway, I mentioned it again in the post about how mage's could have been month or so ago, but here's proposal.
<br />
Consider this spell line for mage defence and group desirability:
<br />

<br />
SHIELD OF E'CI
<br />
When cast on target, they get a CR buff, but prime effect is, when target is struck, it triggers a spell (summoning) coating the target in ice, thus effectively stunning them for a short period. This CAN effect "unstunnables" since it's not a normal stun, they "break out" of the ice in a few seconds.
<br />

<br />
have varying levels of this, each level has a maximum level cap of creatures it will effect. Say a lvl 50 version only stunning mobs up to lvl 55, 55 version mosb lvl 55 to 60 and so on.
<br />
Regarding "boss mobs" these could be flagged unaffected or perhaps merely a 0 second stun if devs want for game balance (0 second stun resetting their combat clock and thus providing a SMALL reduction in damage out put, if I remember the melee system correctly?)
<br />

<br />
Two basic type sof this spell: group and Self only.
<br />
The group version has small but significant chance to go off per hit, 15% 20%? something like that?? and enemy stunned 2 seconds or so, short duration.
<br />
Self only version goes of WAY more, 50%? Giving the mage some breathing space and a chance ot live.
<br />

<br />
Resist is CHROMATIC, it can be avoided just hard, and cold resist has no effect per se since it COATS you in ice, it doesn't actually affect you with cold.
<br />

<br />
Thus mages would be wanted in groups and raids, and have some more safety. Note for raids tough it is a group spell, obviously it needs refreshing, and it helps EVERYONE ergo it owuld be a wanted buff and 1 mage isn't likely to cut it for providing this service, ergo more than 1 mage is desirable. Note having mosb hitting for 500+ stunned for a few seconds automatically isn't to be sniffed at when you are getting smeared.
