			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I like this idea also, however, there's definately some balance issues to think about. Good addressing though.
<br />

<br />
- low chance to proc the stun on the mob. 15% may be about right. However, perhaps temper it to about 15% of the time, not 15% of all hits, similar to how weapon procs are. Making it too strong for fast hitting mobs can be a problem for balance later.
<br />

<br />
- This is going to come in as 'environmental' damage, or an environmental stun. Are NPC's affected by environmental effects such as that?
<br />

<br />
- The stun would be a random duration, likely, since almost all stuns tend to be. 2 seconds isn't a terribly long time, either, since it's likely to happen when the mob's attack round is complete. Is this a way to delay the next round by 2 seconds, or will the mob's attack round refresh while stunned (most mobs, unless hard and fast hitting, hit with a delay around 30ish)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
